<inglise>(13.12.2001 entered into force 10.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 102, 667) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud saastetasu m&auml;&auml;rasid suurendatakse: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The pollution charge rates provided for in subsection (1) of this section are increased by a factor of: </inglise>
<eesti>1) 1,2 korda Narva j&otilde;ega piirnevate omavalitsus&uuml;ksuste piires asuvate paiksete saasteallikate puhul, kui saasteainete v&auml;ljumisk&otilde;rgus on &uuml;le 100 meetri maapinnast; </eesti>
<inglise>1) 1.2 in the case of stationary sources of pollution located within the boundaries of local governments bordering on the Narva River, if the height of release of pollutants is more than 100 metres above ground level; </inglise>
<eesti>2) 1,5 korda J&otilde;hvis, Kivi&otilde;lis, Kohtla-J&auml;rvel, Narvas, Sillam&auml;el ja Tartus asuvate paiksete saasteallikate puhul; </eesti>
<inglise>2) 1.5 in the case of stationary sources of pollution located in J&otilde;hvi, Kivi&otilde;li, Kohtla-J&auml;rve, Narva, Sillam&auml;e or Tartu; </inglise>
<eesti>3) 2 korda Tallinnas asuvate paiksete saasteallikate puhul; </eesti>
<inglise>3) 2 in the case of stationary sources of pollution located in Tallinn; </inglise>
<eesti>4) 2,5 korda Haapsalus, Kuressaares, Narva-J&otilde;esuus ja P&auml;rnus asuvate paiksete saasteallikate puhul. </eesti>
<inglise>4) 2.5 in the case of stationary sources of pollution located in Haapsalu, Kuressaare, Narva-J&otilde;esuu or P&auml;rnu; </inglise>
<eesti>(3) S&uuml;sinikdioksiidi (CO <hi rend="sub"> 2 </hi>) v&auml;lis&otilde;hku viimise eest maksab saastetasu energiaettev&otilde;tja, kelle saasteallika p&otilde;letusseadmete nimisoojusv&otilde;imsused on kokku &uuml;le 50 megavati. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If the total rated thermal input of the combustion plants of a source of pollution of an energy undertaking is greater than 50 megawatts, the energy undertaking shall pay the pollution charge for release of carbon dioxide (CO <hi rend="sub"> 2 </hi>) into ambient air. </inglise>
