<inglise>(5) In addition to the pollution charge rates established in subsection (1) of this section, if the pH of waste water directed into a water body is greater than 9.0 or less than 6.0, the pollution charge shall be paid at a rate of 42 cents as of 1 January 2002, 50 cents as of 1 January 2003, 60 cents as of 1 January 2004 and 73 cents as of 1 January 2005 per each 0.1 pH unit by which the pH of the waste water is greater than 9.0 or less than 6.0 per cubic metre of waste water. </inglise>
